@Corine This sounds like a little bit too much flour may have been added. Adding 1/4 cup of water to this recipe would have yielded a dough at nearly 80% hydration which is on the higher end. An 80% hydration dough (depending of the success of gluten development) would look anything from a soft, silky, stretchy dough to a gloppy mess.

The recipe as written, would yield a dough just under 60% hydration which is typical of sweet roll doughs. 60% hydration is the sweet spot for a manageable and versatile dough. Not sticky after mixing and will take a good shaping when properly relaxed.

I’m a full-time baker and would highly recommend using a scale to measure out ingredients. Baking is much more of an exact science than most expect, Happy Baking!
